The paper discusses the use of citation networks and the PageRank algorithm to measure the academic reputation of institutions in different research fields. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, given the focus on bibliometric data and citation patterns, we believe that cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, followed by cs.SI, cs.SD, and cs.CY.
